          <physDesc>
            <p> Vellum, about 14 3/4 in. by 11 3/4, consisting of 135 leaves, some of which are much stained and torn, especially foll.5, 9, 10, 49, 56, 59, 60, 62, 68, 100, 134 and 135. Owing to the imperfect condition of the volume, the number of quires cannot be accurately stated; nor does it appear how they were originally signed. At present, the last signature is ܠܒ(fol. 125a).Leaves are wanting at the beginning and end, as well as after foll. 1, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 49, 52, 65, 68, 70, 81, 84, 87, 99, 101, 133 and134. Each page is divided into two columns, of from 15 to 21 lines. The writing is a large, beautiful  Estrangela of the vith cent</p>
